'''B. D. Satoskar''' (26 March 1909 – 27 November 2000) was a historian, [[freedom fighter]], publisher and journalist from the state of [[Goa]], India.  He was born in [[Mashel]] village of Goa.  Satoskar has authored many books in [[Marathi language|Marathi]] as well as [[Konkani language|Konkani]].  He is best known for ''Gomantak prakriti ani Sanskriti'' (Goa:Nature and Culture,volumes I-III), an encyclopedic work on history and culture of Goa and the [[Goans]].<ref name=bd>{{cite book|title=Journal of South Asian Literature, Volume 18|year=1983|publisher=Asian Studies Center, Michigan State University.,|location=Michigan State University. Asian Studies Center|page=284}}</ref> This work was republished on occasion of his birth centenary, in March 2009.

==Legacy==
The Directorate of Official Language, [[Government of Goa]] has instituted the ''B. D. Satoskar Marathi Bhasha Puraskar'' under the Bhasha Puraskar Yojana. The award is conferred upon personalities to honour their contribution to [[Marathi language]]. The award consists of [[Indian rupee|Rupees]] One [[Lakh]],    memento, manpatra, [[shawl]] and a shriphal.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20180621114522/http://goadpse.gov.in/Explanatory%20Memorandum%202015-16.pdf</ref><ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20180621114706/http://goaprintingpress.gov.in/downloads/1819/1819-12-SII-OG-0.pdf</ref>

