{{EngvarB|date=July 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Karun Thapa | image = Karun-Thapa-Photo.jpg | caption = Karun Thapa | native_name = करुण थापा | native_name_lang = NP | birth_date = 1965/03/23 | birth_place = Beni Bazaar, Myagdi, Nepal | residence = Basundhara, Tokha Municipality, Kathmandu, Nepal | nationality = Nepali | other_names = T. Karun | occupation = IT Professional, Film Editor, 3D Animator, Trainer, Lyricist | years active = 1986–Present | spouse = Tsering Lama (Sareeta Thapa) | children = Purnima Thapa, Swikriti Thapa, Suhanee Thapa }} '''Karun Thapa''' ([[Nepali language|Nepali]]: करुण थापा) born on March 23, 1965) is a [[Nepal]]i IT expert,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ictframe.com/age-of-apps/|title=Age of Apps {{!}} ICT Frame Technology|website=ictframe.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref> film editor,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1086715/|title=Karun Thapa|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref> 3D animator,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.everestfilmacademy.com/our-team/faculty-members/visual-editing-department/|title=Visual Editing DepartmentEverest Film Academy {{!}} Everest Film Academy|website=www.everestfilmacademy.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref> trainer,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://aachulay.blogspot.com/2010/08/aachuley-lepcha-community-radio.html|title=Aachuley . A Bilingual Journal illustrating the Lepcha way of life: Aachuley’ Lepcha Community Radio|last=Lepcha|first=Azuk|date=2010-08-19|website=Aachuley . A Bilingual Journal illustrating the Lepcha way of life|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ccdbd.org/Programs/Award%20Program/director_ahivements.html|title=Home|website=www.ccdbd.org|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tibet.ca/tibet/public/en/library/wtn/7409|title=Canada Tibet Committee {{!}} Library {{!}} WTN|last=Committee|first=Canada Tibet|website=www.tibet.ca|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tibet.net/2009/08/cta-staff-participates-in-climate-change-and-multimedia-communication-workshop/|title=CTA Staff participates in Climate change and Multimedia communication workshop|date=2009-08-31|work=Central Tibetan Administration|access-date=2017-07-01|language=en-US}}</ref> a well-known lyricist<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2017-05-29|title=Siudo Ko Sindoor|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siudo_Ko_Sindoor&oldid=782869290|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nepalisongchord.com/lyricist/Karun_Thapa|title=NepaliSongChord::Karun Thapa|website=www.nepalisongchord.com|access-date=2017-07-01}}</ref> and Ghazal writer. Karun is known for his technological contribution to Nepali IT and media industry. He has contributed by introducing Devanagari fonts in computers, introducing AVID Digital Film Editing system in Nepal and introducing 3D animation in Nepal.
== Early life and education == Karun Thapa was born in 1965 (BS 2022) in [[Beni Bazaar]] to a [[Hindu]] family. Karun studied till class 3 in his village school called Dhaulagiri School. He stood first in Myagdi district in a scholarship exam, got scholarship and went to [[Budhanilkantha School]] in [[Kathmandu]]. After completing high school from [[Budhanilkantha School]], Karun went to [[Amrit Science College|Amrit Science College (ASCOL)]] to complete his intermediate in science and graduation in Computer Science from [[Priyadarshini College of Computer Sciences|Priyadarshini College]].
== Career == Karun Thapa started his career a [[software developer]] and a computer trainer. He started making business software for hotels, banks, business companies, etc. and started a computer training institute in 1988.
Thapa was the first person to develop Nepali (Devanagari) font on Apple IIe and Apple Macintosh computers. UNESCO nominated Thapa to participate in the Asian Federation of Natural Language Processing (AIT, Bangkok) 1992 and the Asia Pacific Regional Seminar on Information Technology and Newspaper Publishing<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0010/001051/105162e.pdf|title=http://unesdoc.unesco.org|last=|first=|date=April 11–14, 1995|website=http://unesdoc.unesco.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> in Madras (from April 11–14, 1995) in recognition to the font development done by him. He also developed [[Limbu script|Limbu (Srijunga) Script]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2011-06-03/kainla-and-his-third-dimension.html|title=Kainla and his third dimension|last=|first=|date=|work=Kantipur Publication|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> and Rai ([[Wambule Script]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.opgenort.nl/publication/adopting_limbu_script_wambule|title=On adopting the Limbu script for Wambule|last=|first=|date=|website=http://www.opgenort.nl|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> in 1994. He is mentioned in the history section in a book called ''History, Culture and Customs of Sikkim'' (J. R. Subba).<ref>{{Cite book|title=History, Culture and Customs of Sikkim|last=Subba|first=J. R.|publisher=|year=2011|isbn=|location=New Delhi|pages=xxx}}</ref> Thapa introduced 3D animation in Nepal and he is the first 3D animator in Nepal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fridayweekly.com.np/uploads/issue/pdf/friday_issue_178.pdf|title=Friday Weekly - Caught by the Animation Bug|last=|first=|date=|website=http://www.fridayweekly.com.np|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
Karun Introduced AVID film editing <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bossnepal.com/versatile-video-editor-shiva-puri/|title=Shiva Puri|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> and digital cinema in Nepal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livingwithict.com/%E0%A4%8F%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%B0/|title=The Pioneer of Animation- Karun Thapa|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nepalkhabar.com/np/news/magazine/12720/?tpl=150|title=अचेल सिनेमाको पोस्ट प्रोडक्सन एजेन्टका हातमा छ|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemasansar.com/latest_news.php?id=278|title=रेखाको फिल्मलाई सर्वाधिक अवार्ड - Karun Thapa Awarded|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
