{{expand Chinese|李榮浩|date=August 2015}}
{{Infobox Chinese-language singer and actor | name = Li Ronghao | image = File:Li Ronghao at KKBOX Music Awards (2015-02-08)a.jpg height = 183cm | image_size = 250 | alt = | caption = Li Ronghao in 2015 | tradchinesename = 李榮浩 | pinyinchinesename = Lǐ Rónghào | pojchinesename = Lí Êng-hō | birth_name = | ethnicity = [[Hui people|Hui]] | ancestry = | origin = | birth_date = {{b-da|11 July 1985}} | birth_place = [[Bengbu]], [[Anhui]], [[China]] | death_place = | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | othername = | occupation = singer, producer | genre = | instrument =[[Vocal]]s, [[guitar]], [[piano]], [[Bass (guitar)|bass]], and [[Keyboard instrument|keyboard]] | voicetype = | label = [[Warner Music Group]] | yearsactive = 2004-present | associatedact = | currentmembers = | pastmembers = | spouse = | partner =[[Rainie Yang]] | children = | parents = | influences =[[John Mayer]] | influenced = | education = | alma mater = | alias = | hongkongfilmwards = | goldenbauhiniaawards = | hkfcsawards = | asianfilmawards = | goldenhorseawards = | goldenroosterawards = | hundredflowersawards = | rthktop10goldsongsawards= | goldenmelodyawards = | mtvasiaawards = | ntsawards = | goldenbellawards = | tvbanniversaryawards = | magnoliaawards = | asiantvawards = | rainbowawards = | goldeneagleawards = | awards = }} {{Chinese name|[[Li (surname)|Li]]}} '''Li Ronghao''' (born July 11, 1985 in [[Bengbu]], [[Anhui]]) is a Chinese singer-songwriter and producer. He has released three studio albums and two EPs, and won the [[Golden Melody Awards|Golden Melody Award]] for Best New Singer in 2013.<ref name=":4" />
== History == Li Ronghao's first studio album, ''Model'', was released in 2013. It was nominated for Best Album and Li was nominated for Best Male Singer, Best Lyricist, and Best Producer at the 25th Golden Melody Awards, where he won the Best New Singer award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://yue.ifeng.com/news/detail_2014_05/21/36428093_0.shtml|title=Phoenix Music News - 25th GMA Nominations|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
In 2014, he released the [[Concept album|concept EP]] ''Dear Composer'' and quickly gained popularity, becoming MusicRadio China's most popular new singer. In September that year he released his second album, ''Ronghao Li''. This album won the Best Chinese Album award as well as the Most Influential New Singer award at the 2015 QQ Annual Music Festival.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://y.qq.com/topic/yysd2015/review.html|title=2015 QQ Annual Music Festival Awards|last=|first=|date=|website=2015奥迪A3 QQ音乐年度盛典|publisher=Tencent|access-date=}}</ref>
His third album ''[[An Ideal]]'' received average to positive reviews on Chinese ratings site Douban,<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://music.douban.com/subject/26709181/|title=Douban - An Ideal - Ratings|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Douban|access-date=}}</ref> with many critics remarking on Li's slight change of style.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.douban.com/review/7759023/|title=An Ideal - Review - 谈不上惊喜，有一点失望。|last=|first=|date=|website=谈不上惊喜，有一点失望。|publisher=Douban|access-date=}}</ref>
In 2018, he is the vocal instructor for [[Idol Producer]].
