{{Eastern Slavic name|Rashitovich|Utsiyev}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name= Rizvan Utsiyev | fullname = Rizvan Rashitovich Utsiyev | image = Rizvan Utsiyev 2016.jpg | image_size = | caption = Utsiyev with FC Terek in 2016 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|2|7|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Argun (town)|Argun]], [[Russian SFSR]] | height = {{height|m=1.73}} | currentclub = [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat Grozny]] | clubnumber = 40 | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[FC KAMAZ Naberezhnye Chelny|KAMAZ Naberezhnye Chelny]] | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]] | years1 = 2005– | clubs1 = [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat Grozny]] | caps1 = 222 | goals1 = 6 | years2 = 2007 | clubs2 = → [[FC Kavkaztransgaz-2005 Ryzdvyany|Kavkaztransgaz-2005 Ryzdvyany]] (loan) | caps2 = 13 | goals2 = 2 | nationalyears1 = 2007 | nationalteam1 = [[Russia national under-19 football team|Russia U-19]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 1 December 2018 }}
'''Rizvan Rashitovich Utsiyev''' ({{lang-ru|Ризван Рашитович Уциев}}; born 7 February 1988) is a [[Russia]]n [[Association football|football]] [[right-back]] of [[Chechen people|Chechen]] origin who plays for [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat]].
==Career== Utsiyev made his professional debut in 2005, coming as a substitute for [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek]] in the [[Russian Premier League]] game against [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv]].
In the second part of 2007 season he was loaned to [[Russian Second Division]]'s [[FC Kavkaztransgaz-2005 Ryzdvyany|Kavkaztransgaz-2005]] alongside his Terek teammate [[Adlan Katsayev]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Terek official website|title=Katsayev and Uriyev would play for Kavkaztransgaz-2005|url=http://fc-terek.ru/content/view/112/9/|language=Russian|accessdate=20 September 2009}}</ref>
